# 02-domain-boundaries.mdc

---
description: Marketplace domain rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Maintain these domain boundaries:

User (Identity) ≠ Provider Profile ≠ Customer Profile ≠ Service Listing.

User (authentication identity):
- Login credentials
- Account status
- Role assignment
- Must not contain marketplace profile fields

Provider Profile (business identity):
- Provider information
- Display / contact / media / languages / settings / visibility
- Reputation belongs to future phases, not listings

Customer Profile (customer identity):
- Display / avatar / contact / preferences / settings
- Must not contain favorites, booking history, or reviews

Service Listing:
- Individual service offering
- Pricing
- Description
- Availability information

Rules:

- Never merge User and Profile concepts.
- Never merge Provider Profile and Customer Profile.
- Never merge provider and listing concepts.
- A User may exist without either profile.
- A User may have a Customer Profile, a Provider Profile, or eventually both.
- Providers may exist without listings.
- Listings must support simple publishing.
- Advanced listing fields must remain optional.
- Categories must support unlimited growth.

Core domains:

- Identity
- Users
- Providers
- Customers
- Listings
- Categories
- Search
- Messaging
- Bookings
- Payments
- Reviews
- Notifications
- Administration
